Subject: [PATCH 15/21] tdm/line_ctrl:make Zarlink Slic module optional

According to Kconfig, the module is not selected by default.
so modify the Makefile to make the module optional

Signed-off-by: Wei Yang <Wei.Yang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/tdm/line_ctrl/Makefile |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/tdm/line_ctrl/Makefile b/drivers/tdm/line_ctrl/Makefile
index 8eb88fb..d038d4d 100644
--- a/drivers/tdm/line_ctrl/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/tdm/line_ctrl/Makefile
@@ -2,5 +2,5 @@
 # Makefile for the TDM line control drivers.
 #
 
-obj-y		+= slic_zarlink.o
+obj-$(CONFIG_SLIC_ZARLINK)		+= slic_zarlink.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_PQ_MDS_T1)		+= pq_mds_t1.o
